        {
          "id": 65375,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Reconstituted BCG</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">While taking a brief pause in the hospital cafeteria, you notice your junior colleague distressed, clutching her previous year&#39;s examination paper. Upon inquiry, you discover her concern is related to a question about vaccine storage in an Ice-Lined Refrigerator (ILR). She seeks clarity on which vaccines are typically stored in the ILR&#39;s lowest compartment. You decide to assist her in understanding this by presenting a scenario that includes all the options except one. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Which of the following vaccines is NOT stored in the lowest compartment of an ILR?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4390703",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 32981,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        13
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. B) Hep B</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Hepatitis B vaccine </strong>is <strong>not typically stored in the lowest compartment of an ILR</strong>. The <strong>lowest compartment </strong>is generally reserved for <strong>vaccines sensitive to freezing</strong>, as it is the coldest part of the refrigerator.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/22/picture4.jpg\" style=\"height:384px; width:500px\" /></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A. MMR vaccine,</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> being <strong>sensitive to freezing</strong>, is usually <strong>stored in the lower compartments of an ILR </strong>to maintain its required cold temperature without freezing.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option C. OPV</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">, <strong>sensitive to higher temperatures </strong>but <strong>not to freezing</strong>, is often <strong>placed in the lower compartments of an ILR </strong>to keep it cool enough.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D. Reconstituted BCG</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">, once mixed, has a <strong>very short shelf life and requires storage in the lower compartments of an ILR </strong>to maintain its efficacy.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Heat sensitive vaccines are kept in the lowest part of ILR.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The <strong>heat sensitive vaccines are OPV</strong>, <strong>Reconstituted BCG </strong>and <strong>Measles vaccine</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The freeze sensitive vaccines include <strong>Hep B &gt; HPV &gt;DPT &gt;DT &gt; TT</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The freeze sensitive vaccines are kept at the top of the ILR.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref</span></span></u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: Nelson 21<sup>st</sup> Edition.</span></span></strong></p>",
