        {
          "id": 65500,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Live vaccines can be administered together at a different place in a same day</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 65501,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Live vaccines can be administered at the same place with a time duration of 4 weeks</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 65502,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Oral Polio vaccine and rota vaccines are killed vaccines, that&rsquo;s why they are given orally</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 65503,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Hepatitis B can be administered along with the Hepatitis Immunoglobulin</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">During a health awareness event at a local orphanage, the director approaches you for advice on their vaccination schedule. He shares several practices they follow based on previous guidelines but is unsure about one particular aspect. He asks for your input to identify the incorrect statement among the following:</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4936106",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 32983,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        13
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. C) Oral Polio vaccine and rota vaccines are killed vaccines, that&rsquo;s why they are given orally.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>OPV </strong>is a <strong>live attenuated vaccine</strong>, not a killed vaccine, which is why it is <strong>administered orally to induce immunity in the gut</strong>, the primary entry site for the poliovirus. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><strong>Rotavirus vaccines </strong>are also <strong>live attenuated </strong>and given <strong>orally to mimic the natural infection route </strong>and <strong>induce a robust immune response</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/22/picture14.jpg\" style=\"height:414px; width:1000px\" /></span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">: </span></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">OP Ghai Page No- 183-195.</span></strong></span></span></p>",
