    {
      "id": 16382,
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 65488,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Fever</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 65489,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Local pain and swelling at the injection site</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 65490,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Anaphylaxis</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 65491,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Pertussis-like symptoms</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 2-month-old infant named Mayur was brought to the clinic by his mother, who reported that he had recently received his routine pertussis vaccination. A few days post-vaccination, Mayur developed a high-pitched cough and experienced difficulty breathing, prompting his mother to seek medical advice. Considering the symptoms described, you consider a potential side effect of the vaccination. Which of the following is the most common side effect associated with the pertussis vaccine?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q6165845",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 32985,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        13
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. B) Local pain and swelling at the injection site</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The most <strong>common side effect </strong>of the <strong>pertussis vaccine </strong>is <strong>local pain </strong>and <strong>swelling at the injection site</strong>. This reaction is typical for many vaccines and usually resolves on its own within a few days.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A. Fever </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">is a <strong>common side effect </strong>but not as prevalent as local reactions at the injection site.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">C. Anaphylaxis</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> is a <strong>rare, severe allergic reaction </strong>that can occur with any vaccine but is not common.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">D. Pertussis-like symptoms</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">, including a <strong>high-pitched cough </strong>and <strong>difficulty breathing</strong>, are <strong>very rare </strong>and unlikely to be <strong>caused by the vaccine</strong>. The symptoms described by Mayur&#39;s mother are concerning and warrant further investigation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The side effects of Pertussis Vaccine include:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Redness, swelling, or tenderness at the injection site</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Fever</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Irritability</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Fatigue</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Headache.</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Loss of appetite</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Vomiting</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Diarrhea</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Seizures (very rare)</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Allergic reactions (very rare)</span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Pertussis-like symptoms, such as a high-pitched cough and difficulty breathing (common but usually mild and self-limiting)</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref</span></span></u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: </span></span></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"PT-BR\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">OP Ghai Page No- 183-193.</span></span></strong></p>",
